import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.boxplot(data['price'], vert=False)
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.yticks([])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices across all companies?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    companies = data['symbol'].unique()
    for company in companies:
        company_data = data[data['symbol'] == company]
        plt.plot(company_data['date'], company_data['price'], label=company)
    plt.title('What is the trend of stock prices for each company over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    avg_price = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = avg_price.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Company')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which company had the highest average stock price over the entire period?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(avg_price.iloc[0], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Average Price: {avg_price.iloc[0]:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    companies = data['symbol'].unique()
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=len(companies), figsize=(6*len(companies), 6), sharey=True)
    fig.suptitle('What is the distribution of stock prices for each company?')
    for i, company in enumerate(companies):
        axs[i].hist(data[data['symbol'] == company]['price'], bins=20)
        axs[i].set_title(company)
        axs[i].xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        axs[i].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)
        axs[i].axvline(data[data['symbol'] == company]['price'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1)
        axs[i].legend(['mean: {:.2f}'.format(data[data['symbol'] == company]['price'].mean())])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='ignore')
    symbols = data['symbol'].unique()
    for i in range(len(symbols)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(symbols)):
            symbol1 = symbols[i]
            symbol2 = symbols[j]
            symbol1_data = data[data['symbol'] == symbol1]
            symbol2_data = data[data['symbol'] == symbol2]
            merged_data = pd.merge(symbol1_data, symbol2_data, on='date')
            plt.scatter(merged_data['price_x'], merged_data['price_y'], label=f'{symbol1} vs {symbol2}')
    plt.xlabel('Price of company 1')
    plt.ylabel('Price of company 2')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the stock prices of different companies?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
